title: Far right poised for victory ahead of elections in the Netherlands
byline: By Jean-Pierre Stroobants (The Hague, special correspondent)
subhed: Dutch voters will be heading to the polls on Wednesday, for the second time in 11 months. Geert Wilders, leader of the Party for Freedom, hopes to turn the vote into a referendum on his anti-immigration platform. But the refusal of the right-wing Liberal and Christian Democratic parties to govern alongside Wilders could prevent him from becoming prime minister.

title: Louvre heist: 'To think we could replace the works with replicas is almost to deny what they are'
